CASE
  WHEN condition_1 THEN result_1
  WHEN condition_2 THEN result_2
END
Case statement evaluates a list of conditions and returns a value when the first condition is met.
If no conditions are true, it returns the value in the ELSE clause.
If there is no ELSE part and no conditions are true, it returns NULL.

Use Cases:
1. Derive new information - create a new columns based on existing data. 
2. Categorizung data - group data into categories based on certain conditions (categorize sales on high, medium. low)
3. Mapping - transform data from on form to another (ex, country name --> country code (Germany --> DE)
4. Handling NULLs - replace NULL with a specific value
5. Conditional Aggregation - apply aggregate functions only to subset of data that fulfill certain conditions 
(example, for each customer, count number of orders greater than 30) 
